<body ><div ><div class="mktEditable" id="edit_text_1" ><p style="color: #000000; font-weight: normal;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-412874b6-1cc3-f2a4-f1bb-1d69c858ba65"> </span></p>
<p style="color: #000000; font-weight: normal;" dir="ltr"><span id="docs-internal-guid-7dd283d0-2f41-9087-825d-33bb8500722d"><span><img src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/EUgnl_7cszIGTR1X3eVkmWVHWjFOQWLCILXegcB8MwAhBMjbSzG1F8I4UNHmVMSyAKJv65rGINXs7tDaHNawUKQWaTk2-hALsNfrXkx-DH21WZZj1Dq3qkDZVxNtnQARSvYYGxjV" alt="PIV-NewsletterGraphic.jpg" width="600" height="300" align="center" /></span></span></p>
<p style="color: #000000; font-weight: normal;" dir="ltr"><span style="color: #808080;"><br /><span style="color: #696969;">Today we're launching the first D&amp;I Upskill Newsletter, a new series dedicated to helping you access practical and snackable resources related to issues of diversity and inclusion.&nbsp;</span></span><span style="color: #696969;">The series has been designed by Pivots for Pivots, based on your requests. We aim to send this email once a month, with each issue dedicated to a different topic. Each email should give you tools to better deal with issues you may face.</span></p>
<p style="color: #000000; font-weight: normal;" dir="ltr"><span id="docs-internal-guid-7dd283d0-2f35-938b-c952-73241846a4ed" style="color: #696969;">Based on overwhelming interest, our first topic is "Having Difficult Conversations at Work". </span></p>
<p style="color: #000000; font-weight: normal;" dir="ltr"><span id="docs-internal-guid-7dd283d0-2f35-938b-c952-73241846a4ed" style="color: #696969;">Happy learning,</span></p>
<p style="color: #000000; font-weight: normal;" dir="ltr"><span style="color: #696969;"><em><span id="docs-internal-guid-7dd283d0-2f35-938b-c952-73241846a4ed">The Upskill working group: Papa Akuffo, Amy Benoit, Natalie Bonifede, Eileen Markatos, Andrew McKenzie</span></em></span></p>
<p style="color: #000000; font-weight: normal;" dir="ltr"><span style="color: #808080;"><span style="color: #696969;">Have feedback?</span> <strong><a style="color: #059a91; text-decoration: none;" href="https://docs.google.com/a/pivotal.io/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfiZc8_VMFvNDeNGh4N0npNF632Mrq4UnOYrva8q0TqpnBroA/viewform">We want to hear it!</a></strong></span></p>
<p style="color: #000000; font-weight: normal;" dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: 14px; color: #696969;"><strong>To Read&mdash;<em>If you do anything, do this!</em></strong></span></p>
<ul style="color: #000000;">
<li style="color: #808080;"><span style="color: #696969;">Don't Shy Away From Discussing</span> <a style="color: #059a91; text-decoration: none;" href="https://www.fastcompany.com/3062571/your-work-should-make-it-easy-to-discuss-difficult-topics-of-race-and-equity-at-the-office"><span>Difficult Topics of Race and Equity</span></a><span style="color: #696969;"> at Work.</span></li>
<li style="color: #808080;"><span style="color: #808080;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-7dd283d0-2f3c-c3f5-6c42-b5dfc5264109"><span style="color: #696969;">You Just Had A Difficult Conversation at Work. </span><span style="color: #059a91; text-decoration: none;"><a style="color: #059a91; text-decoration: none;" href="https://hbr.org/2017/05/you-just-had-a-difficult-conversation-at-work-heres-what-to-do-next">Here's What To Do Next</a>.</span></span></span></li>
</ul>
<p style="color: #000000; font-weight: normal;" dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: 14px; color: #696969;"><strong><strong>To Do</strong></strong>&nbsp;</span></p>
<ul style="color: #000000;">
<li style="color: #808080;"><span style="color: #808080;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-7dd283d0-2f3d-9506-9550-cb1fbbfa9623"><span style="color: #696969;">Like any other skill, getting comfortable with difficult conversations takes work. Use </span><a style="color: #059a91; text-decoration: none;" href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1xM0iP6RwQSmx6QqF6Jr0EXjVF3VsYcD0gYvbOnXqgxQ/edit"><span>these role playing exercises</span></a><span style="color: #696969;"> to practice with real-world scenarios.</span></span></span></li>
</ul>
<p style="color: #000000; font-weight: normal;" dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: 14px; color: #696969;"><strong>To Consider</strong></span></p>
<ul style="color: #000000;">
<li style="color: #808080;"><span style="color: #808080;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-7dd283d0-2f42-2ccf-c997-aba6384aa2eb"><span style="color: #696969;">Need a sounding board? Reach out to the </span><a style="color: #059a91; text-decoration: none;" href="https://sites.google.com/a/pivotal.io/inside-pivotal/departments/human-resources/meet-the-people-team"><span>People Team</span></a><span style="color: #696969;"> for informal advice (tip: you don't need to have something "formal" to discuss!</span></span></span></li>
<li style="color: #808080;"><span style="color: #696969;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-7dd283d0-2f43-4db6-664b-dc9501a10e8d">Talk to a friend at another company who may bring a more neutral perspective.</span></span></li>
<li style="color: #808080;"><span style="color: #696969;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-7dd283d0-2f43-8e69-dde3-9f8a79804b2e">Google it. Research best practices and how experts navigate these topics.</span></span></li>
</ul></div>
</div>
